laboratory_examinations.findings: Low testosterone at 2 months: 13 ng/dL (normal range: 60-230 ng/dL for Chilean infant males)
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Treatment with testosterone enanthenate (75 mg/month for 3 months) increased length to 1.7 cm; testosterone levels increased to 240 ng/dL post hCG stimulation at 2 months. At 10 years 11 months, testosterone measured at 21 ng/dL pre and 700 ng/dL post hCG stimulation, indicating a marked increase and demonstrating mature hormonal response.

GnRH stimulation test at 10 years 9 months showed FSH predominance suggestive of early puberty; LH pre: < 1.0 mIU/mL, 30 min: 2.0 mIU/mL, 60 min: 2.0 mIU/mL; FSH pre: 1.0 mIU/mL, 30 min: 8.0 mIU/mL, 60 min: 12.0 mIU/mL.
